<br>
Maybe this will be different on a new server, but I doubt it.  What I'd like to see is better communication between guilds, and perhaps this is the place to do just that.  If a guild needs to get an epic item and plans to raid a plane, they could find out who will be in the zone and work out an arrangement.  Chances are, something can be worked out.  Usually, a bad siutation is caused by a handful of people who aren't reasonable.<br>
<br>
It's possible I'm being too optimistic, but that's just me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ufilatal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Filatal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/19/00 11:03:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Conesus--- FFA planes or schedule</span><hr size=1> Honestly, for the most part the planes are semi-outdated as far as armor drops, Fear/Hate armor is only marginially better to being much less than PoG/Thurgadin/Skyshrine quests.  And most guilds that can do Fear/Hate can probably muster the strength to complete the other armor.  The old planes are mostly for epic quest now, at least in my view, with a few god drops actually still being worth the time.  Hopefully once people realize this, we will see some movement out of the old planes ( except for patch day, when I still expect to see several groups move on the gods for epic quest, hopefully some maturity will prevail and people will work things out at that time ).  But with the number of large encounters out there at the moment hopefully the higher level guilds won't have to run into each other's plans too much.<br>
