I think things like raid boards and posting &quot;I'm going to be in Fear on from X date to Y date&quot; only creates friction.  <br>
<br>
Believe it or not but you CAN have more then one guild camp Hate and Fear without training one another.  On CT we used a calendar system for the longest time.  During its time there was nothing but flames back and forth about one stupid thing or another.<br>
<br>
Finally after the calendar was abolished CT went into a FFA system and in one night all the problems of the calendar were gone.  People were actually TALKING their issues and concerns out with other guilds zoning in.  Working out stuff like &quot;ok we will clear left of temple and you guys clear right.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Now that said I agree that perhaps a *rotation* on Trakanon and likewise dragons seems fair. You can't share a dragon like you can a plane.  A dragon is a mob and not a zone.<br>
<br>
UDL won't support any kind of plane reservation system.  That said if there is a guild present we will always be courteous and respectful of their camps and keep our distance.  <br>
<br>
I strongly suggest that before we start regulating everything that we take a month or so to see how FFA on the planes works.  <br>
<br>
Nephlite Z`Ress<br>
Dark Elf Shadow Knight of the 56th Rank<br>
