<br>
I don't particually like the method of scheduling planes like we tried on So-u-suk Ro. #1 only about 30% of the ppl used the board and #2 only 50% of those that used it even respected it. The idea of scheduling a Plane's raid four months in the future, only to have 4 other guilds show up does not appeal to me.<br>
<br>
Here's a crazy idea that most likely won't fly but who knows. Let me preface this by saying I totally support my guild and friends as I know nearly everyone here does. Those of us with planar armor had help from many ppl. <br>
<br>
What I suggest is have the guild leaders discuss the type of planar armor their guilds lack and what they have.  If the majority of guild A's members have all of their armor except a few folks, then why not have the ones who need armor team up with those in guild B that need armor as well? Wouldn't there be more bang for the buck if a warrior without indicolite went in place of one in full indicolite or cobalt?<br>
<br>
Sure we all want to help our fellow guildmate if we have full gear, but are we really helping them? If more plane gearless folks are in the planes, there should be much less armor that rots, therefore more ppl are getting armor. The more ppl who get armor, the more new people could get a chance at the planes in a timely manner.  Basically, get your armor and get out.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, this would require alot of trust, compromise, and communication among all the guild here. There is also the epic quest pieces and the gods, etc.<br>
<br>
Anyway mull it over, flame it, ignore it, etc. =)<br>
<br>
