<br>
Please don't equate the Council of Guilds (CoG) with the Karana Guild Central (KGC).  They were two separate entities with vastly different purposes.<br>
<br>
KGC = Planes schedules and tracking god rotations<br>
CoG = Promote player-driven events (roleplaying, storylines, competitions, zone raids)<br>
<br>
A number have suggested to me I should create a version of the CoG on AR to further along those ideals.  If I did, the first event would be a chess match in Butcherblock.  While various guilds did schedule a planes day and serve as a host guild (inviting the CoG), the CoG itself did not organize this.<br>
<br>
I know this may seem like a trivial thing to quibble over, but the distinction is important.  Yes, I'm biased because I had a lot to do with the CoG.  I hate to see it cast in a light which is not true to the purpose of the CoG. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#004080">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Unguilded&gt;</B></FONT><BR>
